Here's a complete example:

**XAML**
```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedItem}"
                    EmptyView="No items found.">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="*,Auto">
                    <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="16" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1" Text="{Binding Status}"
                           TextColor="Gray" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

**ViewModel**
```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    readonly IApiService _api;
    readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    ObservableCollection<Item> items = [];

    [ObservableProperty]
    bool isRefreshing;

    [ObservableProperty]
    Item? selectedItem;

    // Fires when SelectedItem changes via generated property setter
    partial void OnSelectedItemChanged(Item? value)
    {
        if (value is null) return;
        _nav.NavigateAsync("DetailPage", new() { ["Item"] = value });
        SelectedItem = null; // reset so same item can be re-selected
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        try
        {
            var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
            Items = new(data);
        }
        finally
        {
            IsRefreshing = false; // must set false to dismiss spinner
        }
    }
}
```

**Key bindings explained:**

| XAML Property | ViewModel Property | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `IsRefreshing` | `bool IsRefreshing` | Two-way — drives the spinner; you set `false` when done |
| `Command` | `RefreshCommand` | Generated by `[RelayCommand]` on `RefreshAsync` |
| `ItemsSource` | `ObservableCollection<Item>` | The data source |
| `SelectedItem` | `Item? SelectedItem` | Two-way — set `null` after navigation so the same row can be tapped again |

**Two gotchas to watch for:**
1. **Always set `IsRefreshing = false`** in a `finally` block — if you forget, the spinner hangs forever.
2. **Reset `SelectedItem` to `null`** after handling selection, otherwise tapping the same item twice won't fire the change notification.
